JOHANNESBURG - If you haven't filed your tax returns yet, you're running out of time.
	
	The South African Revenue Service is urging the public to avoid hurried, last minute submissions. Sars has extended its office hours to accommodate more people. Walk-in centres will also be open on Saturdays, over the next two weekends. Over four-million tax returns have already been filed. The tax season officially closes on 25 November. eNCA